350 g Cheese Tortellini
56 mL Cream
1 unit Sweet Bell Pepper
¾ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
1 tbsp Cream Sauce Spice Blend
7 g Parsley
2 unit Garlic, cloves
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
½ cup Roasted Pepper Pesto
285 g Shrimp
2 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
¼ tsp Salt*
½ tbsp Oil*

Add 10 cups water and 1 tbsp salt to a large pot (use same for 4 ppl). Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Meanwhile, core then cut pepper into 1/4-inch slices.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.
Roughly chop parsley.

Heat a large oven-proof pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter, then the peppers. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender-crisp, 3-4 min.
Season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, add tortellini to the boiling water.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 2-3 min.
Reserve 1/3 cup (2/3 cup) pasta water, then drain.

Sprinkle Cream Sauce Spice Blend over peppers. Cook, stirring constantly, until peppers are coated, 30 sec.
Add garlic, roasted pepper pesto, cream and half the parsley. Cook, stirring often, until sauce thickens slightly, 2-3 min.
Remove from heat.
Season with salt and pepper.

Add tortellini and reserved pasta water to the pan with sauce.
Season with salt and pepper, then gently toss to combine. (NOTE: If you do not have an oven-proof pan, transfer mixture to a lightly-oiled, 8x8-inch [9x13-inch] baking dish.)
Sprinkle mozzarella and Parmesan cheese over tortellini.
Bake in the middle of the oven until cheese is golden-brown, 5-6 min.
Meanwhile, using a strainer, drain and rinse shrimp. Pat dry with paper towels. Season with salt and pepper.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then shrimp. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp just turn pink, 2-3 min.**

Allow tortellini to cool for 2-3 min before serving.
Divide tortellini between plates, then top with shrimp.
Sprinkle remaining parsley over top.

If you've opted to add shrimp, using a strainer, drain and rinse shrimp, then pat dry with paper towels. Season with salt and pepper. Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then shrimp. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp just turn pink, 2-3 min.**

Top tortellini with shrimp.